{
  "stem": "12337.1",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was bashert-- bashert that she shouldn't survive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was so close.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And he brought peasant clothes with him.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He said, I can't take you-- to my father-- but I can-- I can try to smuggle your wife and children out of the ghetto as peasants, like my wife and children.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So he dressed us up in his wife's and children's clothes-- my mother and I.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "My sister was gone already.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we slowly marched out of the ghetto, and we were able to get to this farm with no problem at all.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "The next morning, they closed the ghetto much earlier than they were supposed to.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "My father was in the ghetto, and he knew my sister Hannah was going to come any minute, and she would be caught.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "So as soon as they closed the ghetto, all of a sudden, everyone started jumping.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I mean, young boys started jumping out through the fence trying to escape.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The Gestapo was all over them outside.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And they were shooting left and right and-- and were being killed.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My father, who is-- [LAUGHS] not a big sportsman-- but he just like didn't care, because he wanted to save my sister-- he made-- he jumped through the fence.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And for some reason, you know, it's like a miracle.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "The Gestapo turned his head.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Maybe he sneezed, or whatever, and my father was able to run across.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And he was able to get to our home, and just in time to warn her not to come.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And he told the people that he was going back to the-- to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But in fact, he went outside, and he climbed under the steps, which we had a hiding place, and he hid there.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
